<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="acute-adj">acute <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əˈkjuːt/    美 /əˈkjut/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>敏锐的；灵敏的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His hearing is so acute that he can even hear a pin drop.  
他的听觉非常灵敏，就是一根针落地他也能听到。</p><footer>人教⑩ – 4</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>剧烈的；强烈的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>acute pain</strong> / embarrassment 
剧痛/极度的尴尬</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>(事态) 严重的； (疾病) 急性的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an acute shortage of food 
食物的严重匮乏</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>（数学）锐角的</strong></h4></div>